# Git / GitHub Workflow

Never run `git commit`, `git push`, `gh repo create`, or any other git/GitHub command automatically.

When a commit or GitHub action is needed, stop and give the user:
1. A one-line copy-pasteable terminal command (or the exact sequence of commands needed)
2. A brief plain-English note on what it does

## Example format

> In your terminal, from `/Users/benjaminsteeper/Desktop/OTHER_PROJECTS/heleholo/github`:
> ```
> git add . && git commit -m "add cancellation policy to PLAN.md"
> ```

Always specify the directory to run the command from when it matters. Always wait for the user to confirm they've run it before proceeding.
